												<DIV><SPAN Verdana? COLOR: 9pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: FONT-FAMILY:>&nbsp;<SPAN COLOR: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: New ?Times 12pt; Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:><STRONG><FONT color=#ff00ff>Bards - List Update scheduled for&nbsp;02/07/05</FONT></STRONG></SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal align=left auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: 0pt; 0in auto? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN COLOR: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: New ?Times 12pt; Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:><STRONG><FONT color=#ffff00>1. Raise Melee DPS back to 65% of a warrior </FONT><FONT color=#336600><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: New ?Times 12pt; Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated - DPS for all classes to be evaluated with the class Re-Envision process</FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></P>
<DIV>
<DIV>Equally equiped bards (AA, attack, haste, items, weapons) do around 50% of warrior damage when they are attacking from behind and warriors are attacking from the front.&nbsp; This is below what bards should do.</DIV>
<DIV><BR>This problem hits hard especially on raids.&nbsp; After the first couple of any class, the remaining aspects players can add is DPS or healing.&nbsp; Since bards have such little DPS, after the first two, additional bards desirability in raids falls very low.</DIV>
<DIV><BR>The fact is, every other class can out DPS a bard (though it makes sense for some to perform their primary function such as healing).&nbsp; Why is a mostly melee hybrid the worst DPS class in EQ?<BR>As a hybrid, bards shouldn't be the worst at offense and defense.&nbsp; Every other melee/hybrid class excells in one of those categories.</DIV>
<DIV><BR><FONT color=#ffff00><STRONG>2. Lower Fizzle Rates </STRONG></FONT><FONT color=#336600><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: New ?Times 12pt; Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;><FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being evaluated</STRONG></FONT></SPAN><SPAN COLOR: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: New ?Times 12pt; Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:><BR line-break? **SMURF**?mso-special-character:></SPAN></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>The minimum (max stats) missed notes is 6.1%.&nbsp; This translates to ~55 missed notes per hour (4 second cast time).&nbsp; At the very maximum, with max stats missed notes should be 5% (similar to other casters without specialization).&nbsp; Given that bards use 2 stats to (Cha/Dex) reduce missed notes, it should be reduced further.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The missed note recovery AAs have too little effect.&nbsp; After spending 47 AAs, there is only a 20% recovery in missed notes, which translates to ~11 less missed notes per hour.&nbsp; The cost is too high for the returns.&nbsp; The returns (after 47AAs) should be 90-100% note recovery.&nbsp; <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Notes from Rashere - I’m not going to completely remove the chance to fizzle.&nbsp; I will take a look at the overall effectiveness of the AAs when I have time, though, to make sure they are working as intended.&nbsp; AA cost for the Gates ones has been&nbsp;reduced as of the 12/15 update.</FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Missed notes don't effect the power of bards, it only effects the "fun" factor.<BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=#ffff00>3. Ability to Hold Agro</FONT> <FONT color=#666600><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: New ?Times 12pt; Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: New ?Times 12pt; Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed, chant song aggro was fixed in the 1/26 update.</FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG><FONT color=#666600><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: New ?Times 12pt; Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: New ?Times 12pt; Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG>Bards are jack of all trades, but still can’t cover the role as a surrogate tank (ie. A tank vs. easy content, such as LDoN for time equipped characters).&nbsp; This is because bards can not hold agro.<BR>Bard chant song agro has disappeared.&nbsp; Previously, bards could hold ago by playing chants, but something changed (right before OoW) and bards cannot even use this for agro generation.</DIV>
<DIV><BR><STRONG><FONT color=#ffff00>4. The Modifier Cap </FONT><FONT color=#336600><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: New ?Times 12pt; Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG><FONT color=#336600><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: New ?Times 12pt; Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;><FONT color=#ff0000><xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com<img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-surprised.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>ffice<img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-surprised.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>ffice" ><o<img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-tongue.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>></o<img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-tongue.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG>Bards with good instruments and all AAs can reach the modifier cap.&nbsp; This means that bards are not only limmitted by the instruments they can aquire, they can't reach thier maximum potential.<BR></DIV>
<DIV>With PoP instruments (4 expansions ago)&nbsp;and GoD AAs, bards hit the modifier cap.&nbsp; With GoD instruments, we surpass the mod cap, but are still bound, effectively making GoD instrument mods useless.<BR></DIV>
<DIV>No other class has to purchase AAs to increase their focus caps.&nbsp; Bards shouldn’t have to either.<BR><BR><FONT color=#ffff00><STRONG>5. Better Mitigation </STRONG><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: New ?Times 12pt; Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;><FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being evaluated, this will most likely be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process.</STRONG></FONT></SPAN></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>Bards have the worst melee avoidance/mitigation even though bards are a plate class.&nbsp; This may be a result of our AC/avoidance softcap set too low or simply becuase our riposte, parry &amp; dodge base skills are too low.&nbsp; Many feel that silk casters can out survive bards when they are being attacked.<BR></DIV>
<DIV>Itemization (bard armor) has an AC that is also too low.</DIV>
<DIV><BR><STRONG><FONT color=#ffff00>6. Song/spell fades as it lands </FONT><FONT color=#336600><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: New ?Times 12pt; Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>This is a developer acknowledged bug which effects bard much more than any class becuase the frequency of which we cast songs.</DIV>
<DIV><BR><FONT color=#ffff00><STRONG>7.&nbsp; Left Blank temporarily</STRONG></FONT></DIV>
<DIV><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=#ffff00>8. Concerns for the new epic 1.5&nbsp; </FONT><FONT color=#ff0000>This item was added on 11/19/04 currently we do not have any developer feedback.</FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>Our epic 1.5 quest seems disproportionatly difficult. The effect does not last long, and its recast time is too long.&nbsp; The weapon, stat-wise, is great but the damage/delay ratio is below PoTime weapons (while every other epic is above it). </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The quest requires two tough raids in Dragon Necropolis, a zone that is very difficult to get to, and has little attraction for other classes. These raids drop virtually no other gear that would make a raid want to do them. There are 4 other dragons and a monster in Torment that require small raids. None of the items from the Dragon Necropolis raids are required for the final epic combine, and appear to be solely for the epic 2.0, yet we cannot complete our epic 1.5 without them.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The activated effect has too short of a&nbsp;duration and log recast time for it to be effective.&nbsp;&nbsp;<SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: New ?Times **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; mso-fareast-font-family: Arial; #818181; 10pt;><SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp;</SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>The click effect will be a 6/3 minute recast for the 1.5/2.0. The effect will be made more powerful: The increase to crit mods will be 12% and the accuracy mod will be doubled for the 2.0, and the 1.5 will be scaled up as well. </STRONG></FONT></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Short duration procs/clickies such as the bard epic (1.0) should have the buff icon in the short-term/bard buff window.&nbsp; In many cases players are unable to get the benefit of the clicky/proc due to already having a full buff window or remove the buff so they can have room for more important buffs/heals.&nbsp; This diminishes the bard's contribution to the group and can cause the bard to become a hinderence even.<BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=#ffff00>9. Fix OoW Songs </FONT><FONT color=#ff0000>This item was added on 11/19/04 currently we do not have any developer feedback.</FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>Bards got almost nothing new and unique in OoW.&nbsp; The targetted 15% player power increase just didnt apply to bards.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>Our AoE nerf made our new AoE song (<STRONG>Zuriki's Song of Shenanegans) </STRONG>completely worthless compared the to PoP AE slow/dot.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Our first overhaste song <STRONG>(Yelhun's Mystic Call) </STRONG>is actually a percentage downgrade from our GoD overhaste song.&nbsp; Our ancient song is a slight upgrade to our GoD overhaste.&nbsp; For an ancient song it should do something much more.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Our new mana regen songs <STRONG>(Cantata/Chorus of Life) </STRONG>are not worth much.&nbsp; No one who has a lute of flowing waters would use the new one in a group situation over the chorus of life effect.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Our warmarch <STRONG>(War March of Muram) </STRONG>&nbsp;has the same haste.&nbsp; The str component doesnt do much and while the DS is nice, it isn't much more than our OoW song.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The only new song/ability we got has a recast time that makes it extremely difficult to cast <STRONG>(Verse of Vesagran)</STRONG>.&nbsp; Unlike casters who have these types of spells, our song fades really fast so it can't be considered as a rune type song.&nbsp; Make it last 1 minute or remove the recast time.</DIV></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><A href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=bardbalance&amp;message.id=2498" target=_blank><FONT color=#f0a911>More suggestiong here</FONT></A><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=#ffff00>10. Increase Puretone's usefulness </FONT><FONT color=#336600><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: New ?Times 12pt; Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>Puretone is supposed to have the modifier of the best instrument in game.&nbsp; It currently has a 2.8 modifier while the best instruments have a 3.7 modifier and the re-use time on puretone is too long.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Some have suggested making puretone a 1.8 modifier and a 1.0 overmod to all songs.&nbsp; This will keep the disc at 2.8 with no instruments, but when equiped with better insturments, it will increase their effectiveness (ie. 2.8 drum + 1.0 overmodifier from puretone)</SPAN></SPAN></DIV></DIV></DIV>
																									<p>*************************************************<br>Ashlanne Barefoot<br>Community Relations Coordinator<br>Norrath, where I kick off my shoes and run in bare feet.<br><b><a href="http://stationforums.station.sony.com/communitysoe/ "><font color="red">Check out the Station Forums!</font></a>
																
										</td></tr>
